can I be your friend?

1788
01:39:48,302 --> 01:39:49,701
-What?
-OK.

1789
01:39:50,222 --> 01:39:54,181
Play soccer with you,
go for picnics,

1790
01:39:54,342 --> 01:39:58,381
to theme parks,
go to the beach,

1791
01:39:58,542 --> 01:40:01,579
maybe go mountain-climbing,
motorbike riding...

1792
01:40:02,702 --> 01:40:05,421
and... and...

1793
01:40:06,942 --> 01:40:08,853
and...

1794
01:40:11,382 --> 01:40:13,293
and...

1795
01:40:15,782 --> 01:40:18,535
and hang out...

1796
01:40:20,422 --> 01:40:22,333
and to discos with girls...

1797
01:40:23,302 --> 01:40:24,735
and...

1798
01:40:25,982 --> 01:40:27,574
Will you dance with me?

1799
01:40:28,582 --> 01:40:31,176
Not now, my knee's
swollen up like that.

1800
01:40:32,742 --> 01:40:34,972
You want a separation, don't you?

1801
01:40:36,022 --> 01:40:37,421
You don't love me

1802
01:40:37,942 --> 01:40:40,376
and you don't want
to have a child with me.

1803
01:40:41,622 --> 01:40:44,853
We could have been so happy,
like a normal family:

1804
01:40:45,062 --> 01:40:46,893
dad, mum...

1805
01:40:48,142 --> 01:40:51,452
But you don't love me,
you don't love us.

1806
01:40:54,102 --> 01:40:58,061
We haven't even decided if the
nursery should be public or private.

1807
01:40:59,382 --> 01:41:01,259
Answer me please:

1808
01:41:02,182 --> 01:41:04,457
do you want a separation?

1809
01:41:10,662 --> 01:41:11,856
Private.

1810
01:41:12,902 --> 01:41:14,779
The private nursery.

1811
01:41:19,142 --> 01:41:21,133
Miguel, I'm going to see a lawyer.

1812
01:41:21,342 --> 01:41:22,536
A lawyer?

1813
01:41:23,262 --> 01:41:26,777
But you can come and see the kids
whenever you like.

1814
01:41:27,142 --> 01:41:28,211
Okay?

1815
01:41:28,742 --> 01:41:29,697
Right.

1816
01:41:30,342 --> 01:41:31,297
Well...

1817
01:41:32,822 --> 01:41:37,213
I'm going to sing a song
I composed. I've composed it.

1818
01:41:37,542 --> 01:41:39,533
No, Miguel, don't sing.

1819
01:41:39,702 --> 01:41:42,216
Don't make a fool of yourself
and of me...

1820
01:41:42,382 --> 01:41:46,534
That's enough. I'm going to sing.
I'm going to sing. That's enough!

1821
01:41:46,702 --> 01:41:49,136
Let me do something
for once in my life.

1822
01:41:51,902 --> 01:41:54,780
I love you a lot,
but you wear me out.

1823
01:42:01,902 --> 01:42:03,381
-Hi.
-Hi.

1824
01:42:05,222 --> 01:42:07,178
Aren't you going
to ask me to dance?

1825
01:42:07,342 --> 01:42:10,300
-I'm clumsy, but if you want...
-...to marry you.

1826
01:42:10,942 --> 01:42:11,818
What?

1827
01:42:11,982 --> 01:42:15,531
I want to marry you.
Have babies with you, buy a house...

1828
01:42:17,542 --> 01:42:19,260
Well, maybe a dance.

1829
01:42:34,462 --> 01:42:36,054
We were too late.

1830
01:42:36,222 --> 01:42:39,180
Hello, I'm Miguel Pichoto

1831
01:42:39,422 --> 01:42:43,415
and I'd like to sing a song
I composed especially for my friends

1832
01:42:44,302 --> 01:42:46,293
and for the newlyweds.

1833
01:42:46,942 --> 01:42:48,694
It goes something like this:

1834
01:42:50,022 --> 01:42:51,978
One, two, three.

1835
01:42:59,662 --> 01:43:03,018
<i>What is the question,</i>
<i>I know the answer...</i>

1836
01:43:03,182 --> 01:43:04,331
<i>Tell me</i>

1837
01:43:04,502 --> 01:43:06,652
<i>if I've found the doorway...</i>

1838
01:43:07,182 --> 01:43:09,457
I want to marry you, Jorge.

1839
01:43:09,622 --> 01:43:13,820
The Daniel thing was a mistake.
I was scared of marriage.

1840
01:43:14,262 --> 01:43:17,140
But I'm not any more.

1841
01:43:20,022 --> 01:43:22,092
You mind if we sit down a minute?

1842
01:43:24,702 --> 01:43:28,138
<i>And now what?</i>
<i>And now what?</i>

1843
01:43:28,862 --> 01:43:31,899
<i>And now what?</i>
<i>And now what?</i>

1844
01:43:33,462 --> 01:43:35,339
It's the right thing to do.

1845
01:43:40,782 --> 01:43:41,976
I don't know.

1846
01:43:42,782 --> 01:43:44,374
I should be going.

1847
01:43:45,342 --> 01:43:49,620
My uncle said housing prices
are low. With my wage and yours...

1848
01:43:49,782 --> 01:43:51,773
Our families would help us.

1849
01:43:53,582 --> 01:43:55,174
I've got to go.

1850
01:43:55,862 --> 01:43:56,977
I've got to go.

1851
01:44:01,382 --> 01:44:02,371
I'm sorry.

1852
01:44:16,982 --> 01:44:20,179
This is the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

1853
01:44:20,342 --> 01:44:22,298
That guy's got talent.

1854
01:44:22,462 --> 01:44:24,373
He's really something.

1855
01:44:26,462 --> 01:44:30,137
<i>And now what?</i>
<i>And now what?</i>

1856
01:44:30,302 --> 01:44:33,499
<i>And now what?</i>
<i>And now what?</i>

1857
01:44:44,902 --> 01:44:45,698
Jorge.

1858
01:44:50,862 --> 01:44:53,171
You left your stomach medicine.

1859
01:44:53,782 --> 01:44:54,737
Thanks.

1860
01:44:57,862 --> 01:44:59,295
Well, I'm going in.

1861
01:45:02,822 --> 01:45:03,811
Goodbye.

1862
01:45:04,662 --> 01:45:05,617
Goodbye.

1863
01:45:13,662 --> 01:45:15,141
Are you OK?

1864
01:45:21,582 --> 01:45:23,937
You're a great singer, Miguel.

1865
01:45:24,102 --> 01:45:25,421
Thank you.

1866
01:45:26,102 --> 01:45:28,980
Look, Violeta,
my platonic girlfriend.

1867
01:45:29,262 --> 01:45:33,050
-You have more songs, don't you?
-One more, but...

1868
01:45:33,222 --> 01:45:34,621
Great.

1869
01:45:34,782 --> 01:45:36,818
Well, you give me 2,000 euros now

1870
01:45:36,982 --> 01:45:40,691
